ARRAY 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS IT???
----------------
 	- collection of homogeneous elements
 	- Fixed size 
 	- Index based
 	- it is an Object in java

CREATION 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	
	datatype []arname
	
	//creating array object 
	
	arname = new datatype[int size];
	
	//initialize 
	arname[index] = value;

	//utilization 
	S.O.P(arname[index]);


-------------------------------------ArrayIntro.java-------------------------------------------------

	TYPE 1
	--------------------------------------------
		Array Size is ALWAYS an INTEGER 

		ar = new int[5]; < --------- is it mandatory to give size here? 

		YEAH , YES IT IS ! COMPITE TIME ERROR, SYNTAX PROBLEM 

	TYPE 2	
	--------------------------------------------
		int a = 5

		ar = new int[a]; <---- possible

	TYPE 3
	--------------------------------------------

		char a = 'A';
		ar = new int[a]; <---- No problem, here array size would be 65 
								auto type casting
	
	TYPE 4
	--------------------------------------------

		ar = new int[-2];

		NO Compile Time error
		Just an Runtime Exception -> java.lang.NegativeArraySizeException

	TYPE 5	
	--------------------------------------------
	
		//WITHOUT NEW OPERATOR
		int[] ar = {10,4,2};

	TYPE 6
	--------------------------------------------
		
		//ANOTHER WAY 
		int[] ar = new ar[]{10,5,2};

